The Jazz, stung by a 131-122 loss to the Washington Wizards on Thursday, bounced back by the skin of their teeth as Raptors center Pascal Siakam's potential game-tying shot dipped in then out at the buzzerIn the East, the Brooklyn Nets slipped half a game behind conference leaders Philadelphia with a 121-113 loss to the Orlando MagicNikola Jokic and Jamal Murray keyed Denver's stunning rally for a 131-127 overtime victory over the Chicago Bulls